Package ru.tinkoff.qa.neptune.selenium.content.management

Annotation Interface UseDefaultBrowserContent

@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target(TYPE) public @interface UseDefaultBrowserContent
This annotation marks a class to define how often default content management strategy should be used. Default content management strategy is defined by SwitchToWindow, Navigate and SwitchToFrame annotations on a class.

    • addNavigationParams

      boolean addNavigationParams
      Returns:
      to add navigation parameters to strategy which is assigned to a method. Navigation parameters are added when a test or fixture method is annotated by any/both SwitchToWindow and/or SwitchToFrame, but is not annotated by Navigate
      Default:
      false
